<br>
“GINNY WAKE UP!” came the voice of her brother, Ron.<br>
<br>
“Make me.” she growled loud enough for him to hear.<br>
<br>
It was June 21, Ginny’s 16th birthday. She was going to be a 6th year.<br>
What she didn’t know was that Hermione and Harry were standing <br>
outside her door next to Ron to surprise her.<br>
<br>
“Harry and Hermione are here now!” he bellowed.<br>
<br>
“So? They’re your friends. Its not like they came to see me.” Ginny <br>
mumbled, rolling over onto her stomach.<br>
<br>
Ron didn’t have good patience that morning so he burst into her room<br>
and grabbed Ginny, slinging her over his shoulder. She kept kicking <br>
and screaming as he took her to the bathroom, Harry and Hermione<br>
close behind.<br>
<br>
When he got there, he turned on the shower to ice cold and dumped her in.<br>
<br>
“BLOODY HELL RON!” she screamed.<br>
<br>
He walked out laughing. Then he heard her call for him to help her. He sighed and walked back in.<br>
<br>
“What no-” she pushed him into the bathtub that was full of water.<br>
<br>
“ARRRRRRRRRRRRRRGH!!!!”<br>
<br>
She started laughing as he struggled to get out. His hair was drooping over his face and his clothes were soaked. He was shaking in furry. She quickly pushed him out the door and locked it before he could do anything else.<br>
<br>
He walked from the doorway to where his best friends were standing. Harry was laughing at him while Hermione was trying hard not to laugh. Annoyingly, she spoke calmly as much as possible.<br>
<br>
“What happened?” she asked.<br>
<br>
“She pushed me into the tub full of water!” <br>
<br>
“Wicked! I mean, thats thats bad.” Harry mumbled, while trying to swallow his laughter.<br>
<br>
Hermione muttered something that sounded like ‘boys’ and did a quick drying spell on him.<br>
They went down to the kitchen and were waiting to be served for breakfast.<br>
<br>
20 minutes later, Ginny came downstairs, wearing black jogging pants and a short white t-shirt. When everyone noticed that she was in there, they all of a sudden yelled HAPPY BIRTHDAY really loud in her ears. She laughed and thanked them.<br>
<br>
After dinner, the twins yelled ‘PRESENTS!’ so they all went to the den. They decided that she was going to open her father’s present first. He handed her a long rectangular case. It was a sapphire blue with velvet material. She opened it and gasped. Inside was a golden locket. It had Virginia Weasley engraved into it with little designs around it.<br>
<br>
“Oh my gosh! This is so beautiful!!!” she exclaimed, while putting it on.<br>
<br>
She ran up to him and hugged him while thanking him over and over again. He chuckled and kissed her on top of her head.<br>
<br>
“It came with this huge book. But its not in English. Here.” he said, handing her a leather-covered book that was extremely thick.<br>
<br>
She opened it.<br>
<br>
“It’s in English, what are you talking about? Have you gone nutters or something?” she joked.<br>
<br>
“No, it looks like its in code.” he said, scratching his head.<br>
<br>
“Whatever, I can still read it.”<br>
<br>
“Oh, the person who I bought the necklace from told me something very uh interesting. He said that the locket has been there, with your name on it, as long as the store had been opened, and thats been around 400 years ago. Very odd.”<br>
<br>
When she was finished opening all of her presents, she went outside and sat on her favorite Willow that was by a little stream. She would sit there everyday to think about things. She opened the book that was supposedly ‘in code’ and started to read. She got lost into it, that she finished it and headed inside. She had a question for Hermione.<br>
<br>
“Um Hermione, who is Osmosis Thachet?” she asked curiously.<br>
<br>
Almost instantly, Hermoine replied. (anyone surprised?)<br>
<br>
‘He lived over 400 years ago. He was the strongest wizard ever, other than Merlin. He was even stronger than You-Know-You-Don’t-Know-Who (inside joke, but its you know who) but he used his power for good. About 2 years after he came to his most powerful state, he died. No one knows how either. Why do you ask?<br>
<br>
At once, Ginny’s eyes grew wide.<br>
<br>
“I know how he died.” she whispered.<br>
<br>
“How?!” Hermione exclaimed.<br>
<br>
“When he became powerful, he transferred his powers into this, leaving nothing but his body and soul.”<br>
<br>
“How can we be so sure?” Ron snapped.<br>
<br>
“Its all here in this book.” she snapped back.<br>
<br>
“Ok, if you are so sure, use some of the power.”<br>
<br>
“What do you want me to do?”<br>
<br>
“Turn invisible.”<br>
<br>
“Ok.”<br>
<br>
She held the locket in her hands after putting it on and concentrated. Immediately everyone gasped, then she became invisible. After a couple minutes she re appeared smiling. When she saw that they were looking at her like she was a ghost, she frowned.<br>
<br>
“What?”<br>
<br>
“Before you went invisible, your eyes turned silver.” Harry shuddered uncomfortably.<br>
<br>
“Oh! Thats because every time I use his power, it becomes the color of the orb inside the locket.” she said, relieved.<br>
<br>
“Open it up, dear, lets see whats inside.” her mother suggested sweetly.<br>
<br>
She nodded and opened it. Immediately she was blinded for a second at the bright light then it dimmed down to a silver orb of energy floating inside innocently looking. They all gawked at it and Hermione was the first to recover.<br>
<br>
“Can you look into the future?” Fred asked excitedly.<br>
<br>
She nodded and concentrated.<br>
<br>
They were eating dinner when all of a sudden, her father started coughing up something. To her horror, it was blood. Almost everyone ran up to him and asked if he was ok. Then he dropped to the floor, sweat beads could be seen sliding down his cheek. Then, he stopped moving altogether. Ginny ran to check his pulse and found none. He was dead. And she screamed the most high-pitched scream she had heard before, other than with Tom Riddle.<br>
<br>
Ginny broke into tears and ran over to her father and threw her arms around him.<br>
<br>
“What did you see?!” everyone yelled at once.<br>
<br>
She then whispered to her dad. “Go to St. Mungo’s. I-I s-saw y-y-you die.” she chocked out.<br>
<br>
His eyes widened and looked at her.<br>
<br>
“Go so you can try and see if you can do anything.” she hissed.<br>
<br>
She pulled away and a fresh wave of tears came down. He nodded and with a small ‘pop’, he was gone. She then ran up to her room and slammed her door shut, ignoring everyone’s questions.<br>
