<br>
“I set the weather on my mood.” she whispered.<br>
<br>
He nodded understandingly. After a few couple moments, she couldn’t contain herself anymore and she flung herself on him, crying into his shoulder. He wrapped his arms around her, trying to comfort her.<br>
<br>
“Shh, shh its ok. Will you tell me what you saw and where he went?” he whispered soothingly.<br>
<br>
She nodded and told him. He had slightly paled and understood. He agreed that the best thing for him to do was to have gone to check to see if anything was wrong. After a couple minutes, she calmed down then pulled away.<br>
<br>
“Thanks.” she smiled sheepishly.<br>
<br>
“No problem.” he replied.<br>
<br>
They heard noise downstairs. Curiously, looking at each other, they went down to see what it was. It was her mother, surrounded by Ron, Fred, George, and Hermione. Her mother looked like she was about to burst into tears. She was reading a letter. She walked up to her.<br>
<br>
“Whats wrong mum?” Ginny asked.<br>
<br>
She didn’t reply, she just gave Ginny the letter and sat down. Ginny opened it and read it:<br>
<br>
Mrs. Weasley,<br>
We have found out that your husband’s heart was losing blood because the blood was in his throat. If he came here any later than he did, he wouldn’t have survived. We are helping him at the moment and he wont be back till the 26th. I’m sorry for your trouble. If you have any questions, don’t hesitate to ask.<br>
<br>
Sincerely,<br>
Donna White<br>
Head aid helper at St. Mungo’s<br>
<br>
Ginny sighed in relief. Her father wasn’t going to die thank Merlin. The others were giving her questioning looks, and she handed George the letter for them all to read. She silently hugged her mom and went upstairs to sleep. She wasn’t in the mood for Dinner that night.<br>
                                                           <br>
<br>
When she woke up the next day, it was a Saturday. She sat up and rubbed her eyes. She looked at the clock and saw that it was 6:00 in the morning. She stood up, stretched, and went over to her presents to spend more time with them.<br>
<br>
She got a huge bag full of galleons from Harry, Hermione bought her a silky sapphire blue dress that she wanted in Diagon Alley, Bill, Charlie, Percy, and Ron joined together and bought her the new broom, the Ultra-Star because they knew she was going to try out for the Quidditch Team for her House. Her mother and father bought her new robes for school, since they had less people to buy for. And lastly, the twins bought her new books, quills, parchment, ink, and (without their mum knowing) their new products for their joke shop. They told her to use it ‘wisely’ or else mum would have their heads for it<br>
.<br>
She grinned and went to her closet to change. She threw on a pink shirt that said ‘The Best Boy for the Job is a Girl’ in gold letters, blue jean capris, and slipped on some shoes. She brushed her hair, put some lip gloss on, and went downstairs, auburn curls bouncing merrily on her back with each step.<br>
<br>
When she got downstairs, she saw Harry on their couch looking intently into the fire. He must not have noticed her arrival. She sat beside him and mocked him. When he finally came to, he saw that she was mocking him, and he jokingly pushed her. She laughed and sat up straight.<br>
<br>
“Whats up?” she asked.<br>
<br>
“Just thinking.” he replied.<br>
<br>
“Mmm, couldn’t sleep?”<br>
<br>
“Yea.”<br>
<br>
After remembering what happened yesterday, she looked seriously at him.<br>
<br>
“What happened while I went upstairs for bed?”<br>
<br>
“Your mum apparated to the hospital, and the twins flooed over there. They haven’t come back yet.”<br>
<br>
“Ok.”<br>
<br>
They sat in a comforting silence for a while. Then she looked at the clock and saw that it was 7. She sighed and got up.<br>
<br>
“Where are you going?” he asked curiously.<br>
<br>
“I have to start breakfast since mum isn’t here yet.” she growled.<br>
<br>
“Oh, ok. Need any help?”<br>
<br>
“No, thats fine, I can do this in a heartbeat.” she grinned.<br>
<br>
He was about to ask her what she meant, when she snapped her fingers and the table was set with piles of food on the table. He looked and saw her eyes were silver. <br>
<br>
“So I’m guessing that the locket is becoming very handy?”<br>
<br>
“Yep, sure is.”<br>
<br>
They still had an hour before anyone else would wake up, so she put a heating charm on the food so they wouldn’t get cold. She summoned for her Poem Book so she could write in it while she was waiting for the others to get up.<br>
<br>
She went and sat back next to Harry and waved her hand. A quill appeared from nowhere and she dipped it in ink that he hadn’t noticed appear. After about 30minutes later, she put it up and made the quill and ink disappear.<br>
<br>
She had an evil grin on her face, and before he could say anything, she was gone. All of a sudden he heard a loud BANG and Ron’s scream. He burst out laughing, waiting for hell to come.<br>
<br>
Harry looked up when he heard footsteps. It was Ginny and she looked like Christmas had come early. He grinned at her.<br>
<br>
“What happened?” he asked.<br>
<br>
“I got one of my presents from the twins and used it on Ron.”<br>
<br>
“And what happened?”<br>
<br>
“Fireworks exploded right next to his ear.”<br>
<br>
At this, he burst out laughing even more. All of a sudden, you could hear Ron’s thundering footsteps coming downstairs. Ginny’s smile all of a sudden faded and she quickly hid behind Harry for help. Ron came in and the left side of his face was covered in red, white, and blue stars that came from the explosion.<br>
<br>
“Where the bloody hell did my sister go?” he yelled.<br>
<br>
“She ran back into her room.” Harry replied as calmly as possible.<br>
<br>
He stomped back out. When she was sure he was gone, she came out from behind Harry and hugged him.<br>
<br>
“Thank you so much! He would have had my head for that.”<br>
<br>
“No problem.”<br>
<br>
Now you could hear a bunch of footsteps coming downstairs after they heard the commotion. Hermione was the first to come out.<br>
<br>
“What happened?” she asked, curiously.<br>
<br>
Ron was right behind her.<br>
<br>
“SHE SET FIREWORKS IN MY EAR!” he bellowed.<br>
<br>
“Only to wake you up!” Ginny snapped.<br>
<br>
“Well, you could have done it a little QUIETER!” he snapped back.<br>
<br>
“Whatever. I’m not gonna take this crap. Your food is on the table; I’m going to Diagon Alley now. See you later.”<br>
<br>
Before anyone else could say anything, she snatched her money and supply list, yelled THE LEAKY CAULDRON  into the fireplace and she was gone in a green flash.<br>
<br>
<br>
Ginny came out of the fireplace at the Leaky Cauldron. She stood up, coughing, and brushed the soot off her. She didn’t care if she was wearing muggle clothes, she was comfortable in them. She went to the brick wall and tapped the bricks, revealing Diagon Alley. She went and bought all he school supplies that she needed. She shrunk them and stuck them in her pocket so she wouldn’t have to carry them all day.<br>
<br>
She went to Madam Malkin’s shop to buy another dress because on the list, it required two and she already had the sapphire blue one that Hermione bought her. When she stepped in, the person that was working ushered her to the back to take measurements. She was about to start when they heard they door open and a bell ring. She said she would be right back.<br>
Ginny was in deep thought about the locket, that she didn’t even notice that the customer that came in, was going to be measured right next to her. She reached up and grabbed the locket inbetween her fingers and felt that it was warm. She didn’t notice that she was being watched until the locket grew very hot.<br>
<br>
“Ouch!” she brought her fingers to her mouth and sucked on them.<br>
<br>
‘Whats the matter Weasley?” someone beside her sneered.<br>
<br>
She turned her head to her right and saw Draco Malfoy.<br>
