<br>
“Thanks.” she mumbled.<br>
<br>
She looked from side to side at the dress. He looked at it and saw that it looked stunning on her. It brought out the color in her hair very well.<br>
“I’ll take it.” she told the lady that just reappeared.<br>
<br>
She nodded. Ginny took the dress off, easier than putting it on and handed it to her. She took it and went to ring up the price. While Ginny was getting dressed, she saw that Draco was handing his robes to the lady and said that he would take it too. When he bent over to pick his shirt up, his muscles rippled. She couldn’t help but think ‘damn, has he changed into a very sexy guy or what’. She shook her head and went to the counter to pay for her dress. Draco came and stood behind her five minutes later.<br>
<br>
When she paid, she left the shop without a second glance at Draco. She headed towards The Leaky Cauldron and got a glass of water. She sat down close to the fireplace. She was staring so hard into the fire that she almost screamed when someone came out of it. It was her brother. Then came Hermoine then Harry. They looked at her and sat down beside her.<br>
<br>
“Did you get everything you needed?” Ron asked.<br>
<br>
“Yea, I was just about to head back to the Burrow.”<br>
<br>
“Ok, well me, Hermione, and Harry are going to go get our supplies. We’ll see you later.”<br>
“Ok, bye.”<br>
<br>
“Bye.” they all replied.<br>
<br>
Then, they left. She sighed and got a handful of floo powder. She tossed it into the fire, stepped inside of the fireplace and shouted THE BURROW and was gone in a second.<br>
<br>
The time they had before they had to go back to school went by fast. Before they knew it, they were in the Ministry Cars on the way to the train station. Ginny was looking out the window, silently humming to herself.<br>
<br>
When they got there, she struggled to get her trunk out and when it came out, it landed hard on Ron’s foot. Before he could say anything, she put it on a trolley and ran really fast through the barrier before anyone could see her. When she came out, she stopped, short of breath. She waited a second too long because Ron came right after her, looking extremely pissed.<br>
<br>
“GINNY!” he yelled, his face red.<br>
<br>
She sighed and turned around to face him.<br>
<br>
“What?” she asked innocently.<br>
<br>
Before she could get another word out, he came charging after her, almost knocking her to the ground, if she didn’t put up the invisible barrier between them. He ran right into it and fell.<br>
<br>
“Ginny! You know you aren’t supposed to do that before you get on the train, even if muggles aren’t here.” her mother exclaimed.<br>
<br>
She grinned sheepishly.<br>
<br>
“Sorry mum.”<br>
<br>
